#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.386, sc13
msgctxt "an6.57:13.1"
msgid "Kathañcānanda, kaṇhābhijātiyo samāno akaṇhaṃ asukkaṃ nibbānaṃ abhijāyati? "
msgstr "And how does someone born into a dark class give rise to extinguishment, which is neither dark nor bright? "

msgctxt "an6.57:13.2"
msgid "Idhānanda, ekacco nīce kule paccājāto hoti—caṇḍālakule vā … pe … "
msgstr "It’s when some person is reborn in a low family … "

msgctxt "an6.57:13.3"
msgid "so ca hoti dubbaṇṇo duddasiko okoṭimako. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an6.57:13.4"
msgid "So kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati. "
msgstr "They shave off their hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

msgctxt "an6.57:13.5"
msgid "So evaṃ pabbajito samāno pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe, catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacitto, satta bojjhaṅge yathābhūtaṃ bhāvetvā akaṇhaṃ asukkaṃ nibbānaṃ abhijāyati. "
msgstr "They give up the five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken wisdom. They firmly establish their mind in the four kinds of mindfulness meditation. They truly develop the seven awakening factors. And then they give rise to extinguishment, which is neither dark nor bright. "

msgctxt "an6.57:13.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, ānanda, kaṇhābhijātiyo samāno akaṇhaṃ asukkaṃ nibbānaṃ abhijāyati. (3) "
msgstr "That’s how someone born in a dark class gives rise to extinguishment, which is neither dark nor bright. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "an6.57:14.1"
msgid "Kathañcānanda, sukkābhijātiyo samāno kaṇhaṃ dhammaṃ abhijāyati? "
msgstr "And how does someone born into a bright class give rise to a dark result? "

msgctxt "an6.57:14.2"
msgid "Idhānanda, ekacco ucce kule paccājāto hoti—khattiyamahāsālakule vā brāhmaṇamahāsālakule vā gahapatimahāsālakule vā, aḍḍhe mahaddhane mahābhoge pahūtajātarūparajate pahūtavittūpakaraṇe pahūtadhanadhaññe. "
msgstr "It’s when some person is reborn in an eminent family—a well-to-do family of aristocrats, brahmins, or householders—rich, affluent, and wealthy, with lots of gold and silver, lots of property and assets, and lots of money and grain. "

